  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, the predicted selectivity of compounds 1-3 towards other nuclear hormone receptor targets was experimentally confirmed for retinoid X receptor (RXR)α, liver X receptor (LXR)α, and retinoic acid receptor (RAR)α (Fig. 5d).",
    "Computer-designed compounds 1 and 2 underwent initial in vitro testing to assess their absorption, distribution, metabolism, and excretion (ADME) properties, and were compared to the phase three dual PPARα/γ co-agonist aleglitazar 41 (SI11, Table S14).",
    "Both ligands exhibited lipophilicity values within the range of 1-2 (logD1: 1.5 2: 1.7), which falls within the preferred range for orally administered drugs and is comparable to the logD value of aleglitazar (logD: 1.4).",
    "In terms of permeability through membranes, both molecules displayed favorable results in the parallel artificial membrane permeability assay (PAMPA), with permeation coefficients (PAMPA PEFF) of 3.9 cm ⋅ s -1 ⋅ 10 -6 for compound 1 and 14 cm ⋅ s -1 ⋅ 10 -6 for compound 2.",
    "Achieving sufficient cell permeability is crucial for targeting the PPARγ receptor, located within the cell nucleus."
